text.body:
In the District Court og the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, King County, Wash. Terr.
In the matter of the Application of C.F. Reed No. 5931 For a Writ of Habeas Corpus ORDER GRANTING WRIT
The cause coming on to be heard upon the Petition of C.F. Reed for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, and the Court having read and filed the said Petition, and it appearing to the Court therefrom that the said C.F. Reed is illegally imprisoned and restrained of his liberty by William Cochrane, Sheriff of King County, Washington Territory, in the common jail of said County in the City of Seattle, and it appearing form the said Petition that a Writ ought to issue, and it is considered and ordered by the Court that the Writ of Habeas Corpus issue out of this court, directed to the said Sheriff, commanding him to have the body of C.F. Reed before me, in the Court Room of the said Court, on the 27th day April, 1888 at 2 o'clock P.M. to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning the said C.F. Reed, together with the time and cause of his detention, and that he then and there have the said Writ.
R.A. Jones Judge
Dated at Seattle on the 27 day of April, 1888
No.5931
In the District Court, Third Judicial District, holding terms at ___
In the matter of the application of C.F. Reed for Habeas Corpus
FILED APR 27 1888 W.E. Ledgerwood
